# 🧬 Parasite Vision AI

An AI-powered image classification system that detects and classifies different parasite types from microscopic images using deep learning (PyTorch) and a web interface built with Streamlit.

---

## 🚀 Project Overview

Parasite Vision AI is a machine learning project designed to help identify common parasitic organisms from images. The model is trained using a convolutional neural network (ResNet18) and can predict the parasite type along with a confidence score.

The system includes:
- 🧠 Deep learning model (ResNet18)
- 📸 Image classification pipeline
- 🌐 Web app interface using Streamlit
- 📊 Confidence score prediction
- 🔮 Real-time image testing

---

## 🦠 Supported Parasites

The model can classify:

- Ascaris egg  
- Hookworm egg  
- Trichuris egg  
- Taenia saginata egg  
- Schistosoma mansoni egg  
- Giardia lamblia cyst  
- Entamoeba histolytica egg  
- Plasmodium species (Malaria)
